Test-case name: xfwm4 workspace settings/xfwm4-workspace-settings-001
This will test the xfwm4 workspace settings
<dl>
    <dt>Open Settings manager, then "Workspaces"</dt>
        <dd>Xfwm4 workspace settings should open</dd>
    <dt>Type numbers or use the arrows to change the number of workspaces</dt>
        <dd>The number of workspaces should increase, both in the list below and in the indicator bar</dd>
    <dt>Double click one of the workspace names</dt>
        <dd>You should now be able to type a name for the workspace</dd>
    <dt>Type a name for the workspace, then press Enter</dd>
        <dd>The workspace name should be change in the list</dd>
    <dt>Hover the cursor over the indictor icon of the workspace you just named</dt>
        <dd>The test "Click to switch to [Workspace Name]" should appear</dd>
    <dt>Press "Help"</dt>
        <dd>This should take you to an online manual</dd>
    <dt>Click the "Margins" tab</dt>
    <dt>Change the size of each margin, then open a program in each workspace</dt>
        <dd>The programs should not open in the areas specified as margins</dd>
</dl>